INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("48","1","2016-01-21 16:54:14","2016-01-21 16:54:14","HealthLinx was started in 1997 by Julie Berry with nothing more than a cordless phone and an open Blue Book. Julie worked out of her apartment in North Carolina making calls to try and place Midwives, while spending several hours each day in front of a fax machine and handing resumes over to hospitals. When her family moved to Columbus, business started to pick up. The first company hire was made shortly thereafter, and then several more were quickly needed from there. The first office was opened in German Village and increased company size to 9 employees.\r\n\r\nIn 2002, Julie’s husband, Matt, came on board as the CEO and quickly advanced the business further.\r\n\r\n<em>“Never thought a company could work so collaboratively with a lot of money involved.”</em>\r\n\r\nOffice moved to Front St. in 2002 and Matt Berry came on as CEO that year.\r\n\r\nMoved to Grandview in 2007. Had been HES and HTL until that time, but then had the chance to start offering Magnet services.\r\n\r\nBuilt service lines out person by person.\r\n\r\nHealthlinx has been in business since 1997 and has evolved from a resume provider to a true solutions provider. As the market has changed, so have we. Our clients feel the value they receive for our services is well worth it.\r\n\r\nWe are a female-owned organization\r\n\r\nWe provide leadership solutions to hospitals.\r\n\r\nWe are the only organization in the country that offers this suite of consulting services – Executive Search, Transitional Leadership and Nursing Excellence.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>","About","","inherit","closed","closed","","21-revision-v1","","","2016-01-21 16:54:14","2016-01-21 16:54:14","","21","http://beta.healthlinx.com/2016/01/21/21-revision-v1/","0","revision","","0");
